call. Same for methods of the `Config` class. You can still access them with `[]` and `[]=`. Ruby keywords are fully supported. Invalid names containing special symbols (including `!` and `?`) are rejected. Note that these changes don't affect the `reader` option, if you define a setting named `:class` and pass `reader: true` ... well ... (flash-gordon)\r\n- Settings can be redefined in subclasses without warnings about overriding existing methods (flash-gordon)\r\n- Fix warnings about using keyword arguments in 2.7 (koic)\r\n\r\n[Compare v0.8.3...0.9.0](https://github.com/dry-rb/dry-configurable/compare/v0.8.3...0.9.0)"}
